text: In the words of Sam Cooke, “A Change is Gonna Come.” Remember you are the foundation for our city, state and nation—don’t lose sight of that! https://t.co/CwN7jWiNk8

Every day we must thank the people around us for the change they have made and will continue to make. As we look towards the next generation of leaders and see the challenges we face day in and day out we must remind ourselves that all things can and will change.

As I said to the seniors who live at Brith Sholom House without them it wouldn’t be possible for me to be your voice in Congress. It is those who came before us who have laid the foundation for a better city, state and nation.
It was wonderful to be part of this week’s Black History Month program at Brith Sholom House in Wynnefield.
In order to combat the #poverty facing our City we need to continue to expand access to opportunity and I am proud to see companies like Ricochet working to do just that. https://t.co/qjHz1rL4z1

Although the budget agreement I voted in favor of was by no means perfect, I am proud to say that today members of the Ricochet team shared with me that thanks to the budget we as a Congress passed this #Philadelphia run company will now be able to hire 30 more workers this year.

This week I stopped by Ricochet a wonderful company in Philadelphia that specializes in making uniforms for our first-responders. Ricochet is a great example of a company who would not have been able to hire more workers if Congress didn’t act to pass the budget a few weeks back.
To build a stronger Philadelphia we have to focus on jobs, jobs, jobs! As your voice in Congress, I am focused on bringing more quality jobs into our neighborhoods.

As we said during yesterday’s healthcare symposium never underestimate what one person can do. To all the nurse practitioners, doctors, providers and patients at Abbotsford keep doing what you are doing because it is your work that is going to build a stronger Philadelphia. https://t.co/SVnJw6GyHz
It was incredibly moving and powerful to hear first-hand accounts from patients about how Abbotsford has changed their lives for the better and keep them and their families on the path to success.

Abbotsford Falls Family Practice makes it their mission to provide vital, holistic healthcare services to the uninsured and under-insured in order to give them the excellent primary care they need, deserve, and would otherwise not be able to receive.
I voted in favor of the budget to keep the lights on at Federally Qualified Health Centers in our City like Abbotsford Falls Family Practice.

Nationwide, teenagers are fighting for their lives. They are fighting because they don’t want to be next. They have had enough of school shootings. It’s time for Congress to be as courageous as these teens & pass #GunReformNow!
